      "id": 16,
      "options": {
        "content": "## Finding a specific request\n\nEvery response carries an **`X-Trace-ID`** header (UUID). This ID is also written to:\n- **Structured logs** — filter with `jq 'select(.trace_id==\"<id>\")'`\n- **PostgreSQL `usage_logs.request_id`** — query via `GET /api/v1/admin/usage/logs?request_id=<id>`\n\nTo look up a trace end-to-end:\n1. Copy `X-Trace-ID` from the API response.\n2. Run `GET /api/v1/admin/usage/logs` with that ID to get tokens, latency, status, model.\n3. Search container logs: `docker logs maintserve-api | jq 'select(.trace_id==\"<id>\")'`",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "How to trace a request",
      "type": "text"
